{"TopicId":166545,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Can My Computer Run KSP 1.2?","CreatedByName":"phreakshow","CreatedById":158672,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-15T02:17:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"phreakshow","CreatedById":158672,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-15T02:17:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just want to know if I can run KSP with under 20 mods with the following system. Been looking online, but haven\u0027t come across anything. It\u0027s a desktop. Also My laptop keeps crashing and overheating. What can I do to fix that problem too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003EAMD Sempron 145 2.8 GHz\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E8GB Ram\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E750GB Hard Drive\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003EWindows 10\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003ERadeon HD dedicated graphics\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:medium;\u0022\u003E64 Bit OS\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MoarBoostersRUS","CreatedById":181916,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-15T04:04:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere shouldn\u0027t be any problem with running ksp those specs are more then adquite for stock ksp x64. Do you have a ton of mods installed? Edit: (Visual mods?) with only 20 non visual mods you should be fine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the overheating problem I\u0027d get a laptop cooling pad and check to make sure the fan on the laptop is working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-10-15T04:07:11Z\u0022 title=\u002210/15/2017 04:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by MoarBoostersRUS\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-15T09:24:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223195309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508033836\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158672\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022phreakshow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, phreakshow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just want to know if I can run KSP with under 20 mods with the following system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure. Looks fine to me.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223195309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508033836\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158672\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022phreakshow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, phreakshow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy laptop keeps crashing and overheating. What can I do to fix that problem too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn order of difficulty:\u003Cbr\u003E\nEnsure fans are working and exhaust vents are not obstructed.\u003Cbr\u003E\nClean all the dust out of the fans / heatsinks.\u003Cbr\u003E\nRemove heatsink assembly(s) and replace thermal grease / pads.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 \u0026amp; 3 will require dismantling the machine to some extent. See if google has any instructions / videos for your model, or be prepared to play \u0022find the silly plastic clip\u0022 for a while.\u003Cbr\u003E\nLaptops are a PITA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-10-15T09:28:30Z\u0022 title=\u002210/15/2017 09:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mrcarrot","CreatedById":176291,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-17T15:41:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223195309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508033836\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158672\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022phreakshow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/14/2017 at 9:17 PM, phreakshow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8GB Ram\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere to say that this is not the problem KSP 1.2 runs on my 3GB RAM computer. My Broiled half-a-potato computer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NateisKerbal","CreatedById":181904,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-18T14:45:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223197202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508254879\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176291\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mrcarrot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Mrcarrot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere to say that this is not the problem KSP 1.2 runs on my 3GB RAM computer. My Broiled half-a-potato computer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYours is a potato? I found my laptop\u00A0mixed in with animal slop at my local farm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022It\u0027s from 1996,\u0022 they said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022It\u0027ll never run Windows 10,\u0022 they said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoing anything on this thing is painful, can\u0027t wait to build my KSP rig.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mrcarrot","CreatedById":176291,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-18T16:20:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223197858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508337907\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NateisKerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NateisKerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYours is a potato? I found my laptop\u00A0mixed in with animal slop at my local farm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022It\u0027s from 1996,\u0022 they said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022It\u0027ll never run Windows 10,\u0022 they said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoing anything on this thing is painful, can\u0027t wait to build my KSP rig.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s\u003Cs\u003E kind of\u003C/s\u003E crazy. My older 2004 Windows XP Laptop, my oldest computer, can\u00A0\u003Cu\u003Eactually run\u00A0\u003C/u\u003EKSP 0.25. When I tried 1.2.2, the words on the loading screen and main menu were pink rectangles of varying size and shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-10-18T16:20:55Z\u0022 title=\u002210/18/2017 04:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Mrcarrot\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NateisKerbal","CreatedById":181904,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-19T22:48:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223197936\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508343609\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176291\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mrcarrot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/18/2017 at 10:20 AM, Mrcarrot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s\u003Cs\u003E kind of\u003C/s\u003E crazy. My older 2004 Windows XP Laptop, my oldest computer, can\u00A0\u003Cu\u003Eactually run\u00A0\u003C/u\u003EKSP 0.25. When I tried 1.2.2, the words on the loading screen and main menu were pink rectangles of varying size and shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t tell anyone, but RGB actually helps increase FPS on my laptop. You see, HP\u0027s drivers for the built-in keyboard don\u0027t help the fact that my laptop from 2003 can barely run. So by foregoing them and using a RGB keyboard, I can skip all of that. It\u0027s nice and increases FPS. Also, to get KSP to run on my 1996 dinosaur, I strapped a window air conditioner to the cpu and get my Pentium 150MHz to run at 1GHz. Then I liquid nitrogen cooled the ancient GPU and then got it to run KSP! Sometimes Unbuntu dies of severe lack of ram (only 3 gigs) but this is fixed by stuffing in a large hard drive and use some old floppy disks for paging memory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am lazy, poor and cling to dying hardware, but at least I\u0027m creative.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mrcarrot","CreatedById":176291,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-19T23:32:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223199048\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508453335\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NateisKerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, NateisKerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes Unbuntu dies of severe lack of ram (only 3 gigs)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have only 3GB RAM. My computer, however, is newer. \u003Cspan\u003E2005 Toshiba laptop, windows 7.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NateisKerbal","CreatedById":181904,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-20T14:35:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223199079\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166545\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221508455935\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176291\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mrcarrot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Mrcarrot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have only 3GB RAM. My computer, however, is newer. \u003Cspan\u003E2005 Toshiba laptop, windows 7.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a 1994 something (the label is gone) and a 2006 Windows Vista laptop that runs windoes 10. I stuffed 6GB of ram into it but some days the extra 3GB of ram works and some days not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}